-- Yankees Agree to $85 Million Deal With Catcher McCann, ESPN Says
-- B y   J a y   B e b e r m a n
-- 2013-11-24T03:41:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-24/yankees-agree-to-85-million-deal-with-catcher-mccann-espn-says.html
The  New York  Yankees agreed to a
five-year, $85 million contract with free agent catcher Brian
McCann, ESPN reported, citing a person familiar with the
situation.  McCann, 29, needs to pass his physical before the deal can
be completed, the person said.  McCann, hit .256 with 20 home runs and 57 runs batted in
for the Atlanta Braves during the 2013 Major League Baseball
season.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jay Beberman at 
 jbeberman@bloomberg.net  